1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the sum capacity of a deterministic interference channel, which is a classic problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a specific interference channel model and its capacity, which is relevant to the design and analysis of wireless networks. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The cyclically symmetric interference channel model can be seen as a network of transmitters and receivers, which is a topic of interest in social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The interference channel model can be used to study the performance of multimedia communication systems, which is a subfield of multimedia. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve some computational complexity analysis in establishing the sum capacity for a large set of channel parameters.
